Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text normalization.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses neural network-based approaches for text normalization.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing models that can learn and process language.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses sequence-to-sequence models with character-based attention, which are commonly used in neural network-based approaches.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as text normalization is an important preprocessing step for many information retrieval tasks.
